Day 80 Summary
Today marked the return to Spanish study after the Puerto Rico trip. Due to limited time, the focus was on maintaining consistency through Duolingo and Memrise review rather than a full Pimsleur lesson. New vocabulary included family terms, travel-related phrases, future-tense expressions, and common conversational words such as impresionante, sorpresa, descanso, and negocio. Memrise review focused on practical vocabulary including estresado, energía, enseñar, éxito, and tener éxito.

The main goal today was re-establishing study momentum after travel while keeping the daily streak alive. Full lessons, deeper note-taking, and comprehensive reviews will resume tomorrow as the Road to Fluent Spanish project returns to its normal schedule.
